    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Edit:<br>
<br><br>
didnt list sites cuz the only really important ones are Green Dragon Inn and valley of the silverlode.. the others u can pretty much tailor to your own tastes. <br>
<br>
Edit 2: This deck is NOT INTENDED FOR REALM OF THE ELFLORDS environment. <br>
<br>
<br><br>
The idea is to play a smaller fellowship with lots of evasion, that gives your opponent a permanent -4 to the twilight number on each site under 6 (gimli + talent) and in the last sites can play deft in their movements after the 1st move to further reduce the total. <br>
<br><br>
A Hobtookoke deck... the shadow side is moria, which can cycle through ur deck really fast with all its card drawing and cheap minions that add to the twilight.. it really doesnt matter if they twilight choke you.. you can easily play 5-10 guys at once starting with only 2 or 3 twilight.  <br>
<br><br>
if you lose the bet at the start, you start sam instead of merry and pip.. <br>
<br><br>
its pretty simple to describe.. pippin makes all ur tales immune so u can basically play them at will without worrying about them getting cancelled by anything.  Stay under 6 guys and use sam and the crew to remove burdens.  With Hobbit Sword and Power and Hobbit Stealth and there and back again, you can get merry up to power 13, frodo up to power 18, sam up to 18, etc.. the aragorn is there in case u need an extra character after sacrificing gimli at site 5 or if you are worried about swarm at site 9 he can become the human shield. Bilbo is in there to chuck ur tales to discard their annoying conditions. Boromir is there to help pump the hobbits a few extra times and as a chump blocker in key situations.<br>
<br><br>
Thrors map is only there to pull valley of the silverload (all hobbits heal) as that pretty much negates anything they wasted their twilight on at site 6. <br>
<br><br>
Some matchups<br>
<br><br>
Hate / Sauron Damage : Would initally seem good against this, but Bilbo can discard stuff to stop all the really important conditions, and the healing that goes around in the deck is usually too much for whatever pittances the hates and the weenie guys can deal out, especially since the choke prevents more than 1 of those guys coming out at a time before site 6 anyway.  <br>
<br><br>
Nazgul Burdens: Choke stops them from coming out en masse, usually only one or two guys can play,and before site 6 or 7, steaths and various power adding can usually stop them from being a huge issue. The Witch king can be a problem, but sam / gaffer / frodo can remove burdens like madmen,and cancelling fierce skirmishes and then healing him can really save the day. <br>
<br><br>
Swarm: Choke stops the really big fatties from coming down at the same time as the swarm, but can be a tough match.  Bilbo can wax goblin swarms so at least they dont recur if/when they win skirmishes (which is pretty rare actually).  <br>
<br><br>
The deck could possibly use another hobbit sword, and maybe a few cards changed in the shadow.. it would be easy to pump the deck up a few more cards and add them but i prefer to have 60-66 card decks to better regulate what comes out when.  overall the cycling of moria and the invicible buddha nature of the hobbits are too much.. <br>
<br><br>
